Class SpaceObject

java.lang.Object
SpaceObject
Direct Known Subclasses:
Debris, Payload, RocketBody, Satellite, UnknownObject
public abstract class SpaceObject extends Object
The SpaceObject class serves as an abstract base class for objects in space such as Debris and Satellite. It contains common properties and methods shared by all space objects. This class is extended by Debris and Satellite.

      public SpaceObject(String recordId, String satelliteName, String country, String orbitType, int launchYear, String launchSite, double longitude, double avgLongitude, String geohash, String hrrCategory, boolean isNominated, boolean hasDossier, boolean isUnknownObject, int daysOld, int conjunctionCount)
      Constructs a Space object with the provided attributes.
      Parameters:
      recordId - Unique record ID of the Space Object.
      satelliteName - Name of the Space Object.
      country - Country of origin.
      orbitType - Orbit type (LEO, GEO, etc.).
      launchYear - Year the Space Object was launched.
      launchSite - Code for the launch site.
      longitude - Current longitude of the Space Object.
      avgLongitude - Average longitude over its orbit.
      geohash - Geospatial hash representing approximate location.
      hrrCategory - Human Research Roadmap?
      isNominated - Nominated boolean
      hasDossier - Detailed records on the space object
      isUnknownObject - Known status of the space object
      daysOld - Number of days since launch.
      conjunctionCount - Recent interactions
